{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":44722,"name":"Brian Knox","username":"najak3d","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-02-24T23:11:35.661Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI am seeing this now in two different Urho-based apps that I’m working on.   I see it in \u003ca href=\"http://Urho.NET\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003eUrho.NET\u003c/a\u003e which uses the latest Urho3D source code.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI have a shader which scales Text in Screenspace to control size (keeping it readable at all ranges - we increase/decrease size slowly as you get closer/further away).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHowever, in the View3D and also when we use Render-To-Texture to capture a Screenshot, the result is that the Y-Axis in ScreenSpace is inverted, and our Text ends up Upside-Down.   Everything else about the rendering is correct; the only defect is Y-Axis ScreenSpace is inverted.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHere is a screenshot from our GPS App:  (TOP = Correct;   BOTTOM = Y-Inverted)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/5/506273b200a2f3337a69438a7989218d599e587b.png\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/bt783sNAsnafIA5hV8DijJ5oS3V.png?dl=1\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/5/506273b200a2f3337a69438a7989218d599e587b_2_402x500.png\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"bt783sNAsnafIA5hV8DijJ5oS3V\" width=\"402\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/5/506273b200a2f3337a69438a7989218d599e587b_2_402x500.png, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/5/506273b200a2f3337a69438a7989218d599e587b_2_603x750.png 1.5x, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/5/506273b200a2f3337a69438a7989218d599e587b_2_804x1000.png 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/5/506273b200a2f3337a69438a7989218d599e587b_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eimage\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e847×1053 198 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnd from our Game, still with crude graphics, but the Font, rendered inside a View3D, the ScreenSpace is inverted:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/e/eef041704840cf005f8e43253333e7abe3f54d8f.png\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/y5KnLf3siZJoKmVuiafdYAfi6Wb.png?dl=1\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/e/eef041704840cf005f8e43253333e7abe3f54d8f.png\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"y5KnLf3siZJoKmVuiafdYAfi6Wb\" width=\"570\" height=\"500\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/e/eef041704840cf005f8e43253333e7abe3f54d8f_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eimage\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e687×602 17.5 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e===\u003cbr\u003e\nThis seems like an Urho3D bug, somehow.  I can file this as an issue, if it turns out to be the case.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOur current/kludged workaround is to modify the Y-scalar when inside V3D or doing RTT.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2022-02-24T23:11:35.661Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":27,"readers_count":26,"score":20.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":7208,"topic_slug":"screenspace-y-inverted-for-view3d-and-rtt","display_username":"Brian Knox","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://Urho.NET","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":1},{"url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/5/506273b200a2f3337a69438a7989218d599e587b.png","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"506273b200a2f3337a69438a7989218d599e587b.png","clicks":0},{"url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/e/eef041704840cf005f8e43253333e7abe3f54d8f.png","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"eef041704840cf005f8e43253333e7abe3f54d8f.png","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1334,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":44724,"name":"SirNate0","username":"SirNate0","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/9f8e36/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-02-25T03:10:13.472Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eSo, to clarify, you are observing different results when rendering to texture vs when rendering to the screen directly? And are you sure the texture is not just upside down?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2022-02-25T03:10:13.472Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":26,"readers_count":25,"score":25.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":7208,"topic_slug":"screenspace-y-inverted-for-view3d-and-rtt","display_username":"SirNate0","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":628,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":44726,"name":"Golden Thumbs","username":"GoldenThumbs","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/goldenthumbs/{size}/1669_2.png","created_at":"2022-02-25T23:24:16.641Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eOpenGL and DirectX have different standards for which way the Y axis should go (whether it has to be inverted or not), and I don’t think Urho abstracts this away. There could be a function that handles this in one of the accompanying shader include files, I’m not sure.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2022-02-25T23:24:16.641Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":24,"readers_count":23,"score":19.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":7208,"topic_slug":"screenspace-y-inverted-for-view3d-and-rtt","display_username":"Golden Thumbs","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1004,"hidden":false,"trust_level":0,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_suspended":true,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":44727,"name":"Brian Knox","username":"najak3d","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-02-25T23:52:25.952Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ca class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/sirnate0\"\u003e@SirNate0\u003c/a\u003e - this happens on both Android and Windows WPF the same (HLSL and GLSL).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe texture is right side up, because EVERYTHING ELSE in the scene is in the correct locations, including the “base location for the text”.   For our text, we send the Text shader 4 vertices per letter, all at the same World Location, and use the TexCoord2 to indicate “screenoffset from center” and so the quad gets sized in Screen space.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHere is the vertex shader GLSL:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e#ifdef COMPILEVS\n    uniform mediump vec2 cScale;\n    uniform mediump vec3 cWorldPos;\n#endif\n\nvarying vec2 vTexCoord;\n\nvoid VS()\n{\n    vec4 clipPos = GetClipPos(cWorldPos);\n\n    // Now offset the vertex position\n    vec2 posOffset = iTexCoord1 * clipPos.w;\n    posOffset.x *= cScale.x;\n    posOffset.y *= cScale.y;   //  CHANGE TO \"*= -cScale.y\"  fixes the issue\n    clipPos.xy += posOffset;\n    gl_Position = clipPos;\n    vTexCoord = iTexCoord;\n}\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhen we use this for “screen-capture” we have a kludge, to simply toggle polarity shader parameter “Scale.y” for one frame – capture it, and be done.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHowever, this is also happening inside the “View3D” windows as well, for which the problem isn’t as simple.  We’re going to need to have different shaders working in this context.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSure seems to us like an Urho3D core bug.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou should be able to validate it yourself, with a simple screen-space vertex shader, running in both normal mode, and the View3D, on both Android and WPF alike.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2022-02-25T23:52:25.952Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":24,"readers_count":23,"score":9.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":7208,"topic_slug":"screenspace-y-inverted-for-view3d-and-rtt","display_username":"Brian Knox","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"SirNate0","name":"SirNate0","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/9f8e36/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1334,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":44732,"name":"Golden Thumbs","username":"GoldenThumbs","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/goldenthumbs/{size}/1669_2.png","created_at":"2022-02-27T00:50:14.406Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIf I am understanding this code right, why are you using a custom shader for this? Isn’t this basically just a billboard? Urho has billboards already. Just like, use a billboard and set the texture to the render texture. Well, that could probably result in an inverted y axis too, not sure. Gonna have to test that. I’ll get back to you with my results.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2022-02-27T00:50:14.406Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":22,"readers_count":21,"score":29.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":7208,"topic_slug":"screenspace-y-inverted-for-view3d-and-rtt","display_username":"Golden Thumbs","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"najak3d","name":"Brian Knox","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1004,"hidden":false,"trust_level":0,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_suspended":true,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":44733,"name":"Brian Knox","username":"najak3d","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-02-27T13:14:49.335Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eWe have two contexts where this is happening, neither of which is resolved by a billboard (which as you indicated, though, likely suffers the same defect):\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGameEditor inside Avalonia Toolset – accomplished the View3D UI component which has been wrapped to behave as an Avalonia Render Surface.   The basics for this will be released to the public when we’re done.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSetting up an offscreen camera to capture a scene shot, rendering it to a Texture, then exporting that image via “Texture.GetData()”.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhen I saw it happen twice for two entirely different contexts, that lead to my belief that this is likely an Urho bug.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2022-02-27T13:14:49.335Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":22,"readers_count":21,"score":14.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":7208,"topic_slug":"screenspace-y-inverted-for-view3d-and-rtt","display_username":"Brian Knox","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"GoldenThumbs","name":"Golden Thumbs","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/goldenthumbs/{size}/1669_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1334,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":44734,"name":"Golden Thumbs","username":"GoldenThumbs","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/goldenthumbs/{size}/1669_2.png","created_at":"2022-02-27T14:44:44.714Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eAre you using render textures in both cases or just the one? Sorry if my questions seem a bit redundant, I’ve got to admit I find what you are trying to do a bit confusing. Maybe if I recreate one or both of these cases myself I’ll understand better\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2022-02-27T14:47:09.816Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":22,"readers_count":21,"score":14.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":7208,"topic_slug":"screenspace-y-inverted-for-view3d-and-rtt","display_username":"Golden Thumbs","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"use